            <a:r>
              <a:rPr lang="en-US" dirty="0"/>
              <a:t>These eight tools turn the sandbox from a code runner into an actual workbench. workspace_search uses grep — fast and doesn't load files. dir_tree walks the workspace recursively and shows structure with file counts. install_package is game-changing for data work — agents can now use libraries beyond the six pre-installed packages, and packages stick around across calls within a session. git_clone pulls repos read-only for analysis. data_profile is the most-requested feature — one call gives complete exploratory stats. data_clean provides standard cleaning operations without pandas boilerplate. batch_transform handles &quot;apply this to every matching file&quot; patterns. export_report assembles artifacts into polished deliverables. All follow standard ToolDefinition contracts, all register through the same executor pipeline.</a:t>
            </a:r>
          </a:p>
        </p:txBody>
